lets reduce number of variables

library(dplyr)
df <- df %>% 
  select(date.year:date.min, tempm, hum, pressurem, conds, wdire, wdird, wspdm)

we need proper dates

df <- df %>% 
  mutate(date = paste(date.year, date.mon, date.mday, sep='-'),
         time = paste(date.hour, date.min, sep = ':'),
         datetime = paste(date, time, sep = ' '),
         datetime = as.POSIXct(strptime(datetime, format = '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')),
         month = lubridate::month(datetime, label = TRUE, abbr = FALSE))

get seasons

df$season <- case_when(
  df$month %in% c('January', 'February', 'December') ~ 'winter',
  df$month %in% c('March', 'April', 'May') ~ 'spring',
  df$month %in% c('June', 'July', 'August') ~ 'summer',
  df$month %in% c('September', 'October', 'November') ~ 'autumn'
)
df$season <- factor(df$season, ordered = TRUE, 
                    levels = c('winter', 'spring', 'summer', 'autumn'))

ok, let’s go exploring

color by season

rr ggplot(df, aes(x = tempm, fill = season))+ geom_histogram(binwidth = 1)

color by season

rr ggplot(df, aes(x = tempm, fill = season))+ geom_density(alpha = 0.3)

or lets change representation

ggplot(df, aes(x = season, y = tempm, fill=season))+
  geom_jitter(alpha=0.2) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha=0.8)

NA

once again

ggplot(df, aes(x = season, y = tempm))+
  geom_jitter(alpha = 0.1)+
  geom_boxplot(fill = NA, color = 'white', size = 1)

and again

ggplot(df, aes(x = season, y = tempm))+
  geom_violin()

and once more

library(ggbeeswarm)
ggplot(df, aes(x = season, y = tempm, color = tempm))+
  geom_quasirandom(alpha = 0.1)+
  viridis::scale_color_viridis()

and once more

rr library(ggbeeswarm) ggplot(df, aes(x = month, y = tempm, color = tempm))+ geom_quasirandom(alpha = 0.1)+ viridis::scale_color_viridis()

show variation during the day

rr ggplot(df, aes(x = as.Date(datetime), y = time, fill = tempm))+ geom_tile()

no, really, show variation during the day

df %>% filter(stringr::str_detect(df$time, '00|30')) %>% 
ggplot(aes(x = as.Date(datetime), 
               y = as.POSIXct(strptime(time, format = '%H:%M')), 
               fill = tempm))+
  geom_tile()+
  scale_y_datetime(date_labels = '%H-%M', date_breaks = '4 hour') +
  viridis::scale_fill_viridis()

can we do it another way? sure we can

df %>% filter(stringr::str_detect(df$time, '00|30')) %>% 
ggplot(aes(x = as.POSIXct(strptime(time, format = '%H:%M')), 
           y = tempm))+
  geom_point(alpha=0.1)+  geom_smooth()+
  scale_x_datetime(date_labels = '%H:%M')+
  facet_wrap(~month)

summarise by weather conditions

df %>% group_by(conds) %>% 
  summarise(count = n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(conds, count), y = count))+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity')+
  coord_flip()

show only rainy days

df %>% filter(stringr::str_detect(conds, pattern = 'Rain')) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = datetime))+
  geom_linerange(aes(ymin = -1, ymax = 1), alpha = 0.2)

show only snowy days

rr df %>% filter(stringr::str_detect(conds, pattern = ‘Snow’)) %>% ggplot(aes(x = datetime))+ geom_linerange(aes(ymin = -1, ymax = 1, color = tempm), alpha = 0.2)+ viridis::scale_color_viridis()

show ‘clear’ vs ‘cloudy’

df %>% filter(stringr::str_detect(conds, pattern = 'Clear|Cloud')) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = datetime))+
  geom_linerange(aes(ymin = -1, ymax = 1, color = conds))+
  scale_color_brewer(type = 'qual')

show ‘clear’ vs ‘cloudy’

rr df %>% filter(stringr::str_detect(conds, pattern = ‘Clear|Cloud’)) %>% ggplot(aes(x = datetime))+ geom_linerange(aes(ymin = -1, ymax = 1, color = conds), size = 0.1)+ scale_color_brewer(type = ‘qual’, palette = 2)+ facet_wrap(~conds, ncol = 1)

df %>% group_by(wdire) %>%

df %>% group_by(wdire, season) %>%

daily means

rr df %>% mutate(date = as.Date(datetime)) %>% group_by(date) %>% summarise(temp_avg = mean(tempm, na.rm = T)) %>% ggplot(aes(x = date, y = temp_avg))+ geom_line()

daily ranges

rr df %>% mutate(date = as.Date(datetime)) %>% group_by(date) %>% summarise(temp_min = min(tempm, na.rm = T), temp_max = max(tempm, na.rm = T), temp_avg = mean(tempm, na.rm = T)) %>% ggplot(aes(x = date))+ geom_linerange(aes(ymin = temp_min, ymax = temp_max))

daily ranges and daily means

rr df %>% mutate(date = as.Date(datetime)) %>% group_by(date) %>% summarise(temp_min = min(tempm, na.rm = T), temp_max = max(tempm, na.rm = T), temp_avg = mean(tempm, na.rm = T)) %>% ggplot(aes(x = date))+ geom_linerange(aes(ymin = temp_min, ymax = temp_max), color = ‘gray’, alpha = 0.7)+ geom_line(aes(y = temp_avg), color = ‘darkcyan’, size = 0.5)

daily ranges and daily means

rr df %>% mutate(date = as.Date(datetime)) %>% group_by(date) %>% summarise(temp_min = min(tempm, na.rm = T), temp_max = max(tempm, na.rm = T), temp_avg = mean(tempm, na.rm = T)) %>% ggplot(aes(x = date))+ geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = temp_min, ymax = temp_max), fill = ‘gray’, alpha = 0.7)+ geom_line(aes(y = temp_avg), color = ‘darkcyan’, size = 0.3)
